review_blob: Hazy orange color, has a decent size head that holds strong but little lacing. smells of mild hops, floral, citrus and floral. flavor is very mild/ orange peel, hops, herbs and slightly bitter. somewhat of a dry finish. I am not a fan would not recommend and I probably wont drink this beer again.
beer_name: Fish Tale Organic India Pale Ale

review_blob: Near black, pours a small creamy brown head that leaves a nice lace and has a lot of carbonation. Smells of coffee, malts, and a semi sour bitterness. Somewhat mild tasting, starts with a bitter coffee and finishes with a semi sweet toffee. Ok beer I would drink again if offered but probably wont buy it.

Cloudy gold color (looks like piss). Lots of carbonation, large white head that leaves an ok lacing. Strong yeasty bread smell, but also slightly fruity which makes it smell somewhat refreshing. Tastes of sweet ripe banana and bread. Very lite tasting for a higher gravity. Cheap enough that I would by this again pretty good beer try it. $7 a six pack

A clear caramel/dark honey color, huge off white head with great lacing. Smells of hops and citrus with some sweet and sour notes. Very pleasant smelling. Flavor is mostly of piney hops with some herbs and spice. Has a slightly sweet finish. This is a great beer that I will drink again and I recommend you try. Less than $10 a six pack is a great deal.

Light red/dark caramel color, clear with nice holding off white head and great lacing. piney, hoppy, citrus, herbs and grass is the aroma. Has a decent flavor and beer is well carbonated. Biggest flavors are hops and tropical fruit. This is a beer I will drink again and recommend to any of my friends.

Clear greenish/golden color with tons of carbonation. very small white head with almost no lacing. Smells sweet of ginger and spice with an alcoholic note. typical cheap high gravity aroma. Slightly sweet with hints of toffee and floral notes but has a strong solvency. Dont drink this beer unless its the only thing available and its free.

A clear dark amber beer that has a smaller pure white head that leaves a nice lacing. Has a delicious grassy hop scent. Very flavorful with a nice hop flavor (herbal, fresh cut grass, citrus) nice complexity. An excellent beer that I would go out and look for. A must try for all you hop heads.

A golden amber beer that pours a small head which dissipates quickly. Almost no lacing but has a lot of carbonation. Smells sweet of caramel and honey. Does have a solvent smell to it but its not overpowering. Semi-sweet with a solvency to it right away. a hint of floral and some bitterness follow. Another one of those beers that you dont want to drink unless you are purely looking to catch a cheap buzz. $2.50 for a 22 OZ. bottle.

I had no glass for this beer (I was at a BYOB cigar shop). Aroma was decent, strong scent of orange peel and spice. The flavor is sour off the bat. Has a strong fruit flavor with some floral but a strong solvent taste follows. If you want a cheap buzz from beer go get this right now, if you want a beer that doesnt taste like it has a shot of vodka in it pass this up if you see it. only $2.50 for a 22 OZ. I wonder why?

clear, gold/greenish color, has a lot of carbonation bubbles. Pours a tall slightly off white head that sticks nicely and leaves decent lacing. smells hoppy and somewhat earthy, slightly floral and a hint of sourness. Flavor is a little mild for my licking. Hints of citrus and dried hops with a very mild sweet and sour flavor. has a slightly bitter finish. Feels like a commercial IPA but its good. If your a fan of IPAs and you like Sam Adams, you should give it a shot.

Color is a amber/caramel which is hazy. and pours a big off white head, lacing is ok. Aroma is sweet, fruity, herbal, and a little floral. very sweet up front but finishes a little bitter, nice contrast. has a nice carbonated feel on the tongue. nice flavors but could be a little more prominent. Try it if you see it but dont run out to grab a six pack right this second.

Orange/rose colored with a big off white head that leaves excellent lacing. Semi cloudy with yeast floating in it. smells very appealing with notes of semi-sweet caramel and floral with hints of fruit and a touch of malt. Right away you get the caramel flavor with some dried fruit. Pretty smooth drinking beer. overall its a very good beer but doesnt quite deliver what I expected. I would drink this beer again but nothing to write home about.

beer_brewer_name: Magic Hat Brewing Company (North American Breweries)
review_blob: hazy orange/caramel color, big head that is pure white and leaves excellent lacing. smells of caramel, nuts, pumpkin spice and malts. Smells very exciting. nice medium body, unfortunately aroma is much fuller than the flavor. Flavors of caramel, toffee, sweet and a little malty. Overall a very good beer but not fantastic. definitely worth the price. try it if you see it but dont go out hunting for it.

Clean and clear light gold, which pours a big head that leaves a lot of lacing. Aroma is very mild, it reminds me of what I thought beer was when I was growing up. This is a clean, crisp and easy going down beer that is refreshing. There is a slight floral bouquet with some sweetness as well as a wheat flavor. For a pilsner this is a pretty good beer, smooth and refreshing. I would drink this beer again, its worth a shot. ($8.99 a six pack)

Cloudy dark cherry red color. Descent head that leaves a nice lacing. Nice hoppy, citrus, sweet, tropical fruit aroma. Lots of complex flavor with hops, tropical fruit and spices with a bitter finish. overall a nice drinking flavorful beer. I will definitely be getting this beer again, I recommend that you get it if you see it. I only paid $8.99 for a six pack, great price.

A orangish/ amber color that has a slight haze. Lots of carbonation bubbles, small head with little lacing. Smells sweet of orange peel and honey, with some hints of spices. Flavor is a little bitter right away but you get citrus fruit, spice, herbal flavor and a kind of dry hoppy note. This beer was actually a pleasant surprise, I only bought it because of my support for veterans. Nothing real special but a descent beer that I would drink, and its cheap enough. TRY IT.

Very dark brown near black. Thick, frothy brown/tan head that holds nicely and leaves a decent lace behind. The aroma is cereal, oats, semi-sweet chocolate, and oatmeal. The smell is very appealing. first sip, right away you get that semi-sweet chocolate and cereal. Followed by a roasty, nutty flavor and a slight bitterness. Finishes very smooth with a bitter-sweet flavor. Alcohol very well hidden by this beers complexity. An awesome beer that I would recommend to any beer drinker and a must have for fans of imperial stouts.

beer_brewer_name: Magic Hat Brewing Company (North American Breweries)
review_blob: A near dark beer. It pours a very small head and leaves only a very small trace of lacing. A descent aroma that has hints of coffee, burnt wood, toasted cereal, with a bitterness. Ok flavor that is very similar to the aroma. Not as flavorful as I would have liked it to be, felt a little flat. Had somewhat of a slightly sour finish. I would drink it again if it was offered to me but I wouldnt seek it out. Not worth $10 a six pack to me. Not bad, not great only ok.
beer_name: Magic Hat Heart Of Darkness Stout (2012-)

review_blob: A very dark beer reminds me of a cup of black coffee. pours a huge brown head that sticks well and leaves nice lacing. You get strong aromas of coffee, spice, chocolate and some hops. on the palate you get that bitter coffee taste with a little sweet dark chocolate along with some malt and hop notes. Overall I enjoyed it very much and I will buy it again. great beer for under $10 a six pack. A definite must try for fans of this type of brew.

It is black, no transparency at all (its beautiful). Pours a small, creamy, dark brown head. Doesnt hold long but leaves very nice heavy lacing. on the nose you get black coffee, bitter, smoked wood, and a hint of soy. on the tongue you get cereal, coffee, roasted nuts and a pretty strong bitterness (which I like). More like a stout than a porter to me. any way AWSOME beer, this is what beer should taste like. GET ONE, NO GET 6 AND DRINKEM. A gift at $8-$10 a six pack.

Nice big frothy off white head that holds nicely and leaves a very nice lacing. a deep copper color which is nice and clear. Nice aroma, smells, piney, caramel, citrusy and a little bit sweet. Flavor is not as big as the aroma, but it is very good. Easy to drink and very smooth with flavors of grapefruit, banana, molasses, and fresh cut grass. This is definitely a better than average beer. At about $1.50 a bottle at the grocery store anyone that doesnt try this one is just silly.

Nice thick off-white head very nice lacing. Very hazy orange color. Smells grassy and skunky like weed, actually pretty good. flavors of cinnamon, pine, ginger, orange peel and a little syrupy. A better than average beer but not anything spectacular. The smell got me excited but it didnt deliver on the flavor. its worth a shot though.

Decent head but doesnt hold long, off-white/brown. Does leave a nice lace behind. Dark brown/ black color almost completely non-transparent. Smells delicious, mild hoppiness and yeasty. Nice flavor with chocolate, hops, bonfire, and a little bit bitter. This is a very good black IPA that I will be having again and would recommend to anybody.

pours a large head that holds nicely and leaves great lacing behind. Nice clear reddish amber/copper color. Has a strong smell, has hints of fruitiness, citrus, bread and a tiny bit alcoholic. Has big flavor sweet up front with a little bitterness at the end. If you like this style of beer this one is great.
beer_name: Smuttynose Big Beer Series: Barleywine Style Ale

review_blob: Poured a big thick head which was a brown/white color, went away pretty quick but left a real nice lacing behind. Nice deep black color. Very malty smelling, with hints of toast, coffee and chocolate. has a roasted taste with a nice bitter bite. On the finish you get a little sweet chocolaty flavor. This is a very, very good beer. Definitely have a Guinness Extra Stout, this beer is up there with some of the craft beers I pay $6-$10 a pint for.

Beer is black. Pours a small dark head that leaves only a little lacing. its does look pretty active with carbonation. Definitely smells of coffee, chocolate, a little smoky, a real malty smell. Tastes pretty good, you get the coffee right away with a toasted feel behind it. very robust and flavorful. It finishes nicely leaving behind a light carbonated fell on the tongue with a nice after taste. I was surprised by this beer. This is the best Shiner that I have had and I would definitely recommend this beer to any real beer drinker.

Big thick white head with big bubbles, and descent lacing. nice and clear light gold in color. Not a complex beer very mild smelling nothing really jumps out. The taste is the same pretty bland not much to say about this beer. If you like Bud youll like this.

Pours a pretty full head which is off white, doesnt last long and leaves only a small lacing behind. Looks very good clear dark amber/reddish color. Pretty mild smelling but you get a bit of caramel and spice. You definitely get the spice along with a yeasty taste and some bitterness. Its an ok beer nothing I would say is a must try but if someone offers you one, drink it.

Pours a big thick white head and leaves behind very little lacing, beer is a clear golden amber color. Smells like your typical lager. Has some notes of grain, meal, bread and malts. Beer is very nice on the palate goes down easy, clean and refreshing. Tastes very mild not real complex but is enjoyable for what it is. I would drink this again, the kind of beer you slam on a hot summer day.

Clear reddish brown color, pours a frothy dark white head that goes away quickly, with minimal lacing. Very mild smelling, semi-sweet, piney, gummy, and a hint of a bon fire smell. tastes malty and roasted with a mild fruitiness. Good enough to drink its a good beer but nothing fancy. For the price its worth it.

Very dark brown ale, nearly black. Has a nice thick head that holds nicely with a strong lacing. Smells of chocolates, malty, semi-sweet and saltiness. Has a strong flavor but its not very good. It tastes bitter and dank. finish is heavy and musty. Not a beer I would recommend unless you want a strong beer for a cheap price ($6 a six pack), although I would rather drink their double IPA (same price) which is stronger and better tasting. Not the worst beer Ive had by any means but not that great either.

Pours a nice thick, creamy, tall head which holds nicely and leaves a heavy lacing. Color is a nice clear light orange color. smells sweet with ginger and orange peel, and a hint of zest. Very fruity tasting with a hint of spice, not overbearing but well balanced. A tiny bitter on the end with a clean crisp finish, works very well. This is an excellent beer and a must for any beer drinker. I paid $6.50 for a 765 ml bottle at Marionos and that was a gift for this beer. I would pay over $10 a bottle easily.

Pours a thick slightly off-white head, with descent carbonation and a nice lace. Color is a clear light gold. Smells very aromatic, complex with a strong hop aroma. Taste up front is piney and semi sweet leaving a hoppy bite on the finish. A very good beer that I would drink again and recommend to my friends.

Beer pours slightly cloudy with lots of carbonation. Color is a medium orange color/reddish color. descent head with great lacing. Smells floral and spicy, with hints of hops, gum and sweetness. Absolutely amazing smell. The taste is more bitter than sweet and you can really taste the hops and spices. Although the flavor is not nearly as amazing as the aroma. There is a strong carbonated feeling on the tongue and it has a slightly waxy finish. An excellent APA but not as awesome as I had expected with all the hype. This is a must try though for all the beer.

A nice golden amber color that is clear. Has a very nice thick head with small bubbles that holds very well and leaves a nice lace. aroma has hints of spice, citrus, and hops. the taste is semi sweet with a mild hoppiness and hints of ginger and orange. The finish is smooth and crisp. Very enjoyable, I will definitely drink this beer again and recommend it to IPA lovers. a great beer for the price (less than $10 a six pack).

Pours a large head that holds very nice and leaves excellent lacing. Light gold in color and mostly clear with a little cloudiness. Smells amazing a strong hoppy and piney aroma that tingles the nostrils very nicely. up front you get flavors of hops, citrus, ginger and soda. On the back you get that piney bitter taste and the finish is somewhat grassy, but it works well. An above average beer that is worth a shot at this price ($8.99/6 pack) and a must for IPA lovers.

Pours with a small/medium white head, didnt hold long. Color is a very light red/amber which is clear and slightly translucent. has a nice strong aroma with notes of fruit (banana being prominent), and floral scents. Taste is somewhat mild but nice and complex with hints of fruit, nuts, spice, and sweetness but nothing really stands out. Has a somewhat carbonated tingle on the tongue and finishes a little spicy. A very nice beer that I would recommend to some one that like s this style but not for everyone. I will have it again. Very, very good beer but not great.

Pours with a small head that disappears quickly, but has nice lacing. Smells of bourbon scotch, caramel, malty, and syrupy. Color is a dark red/light brown and a tiny bit hazy. Amazing flavor with hints of scotch, caramel, slightly woody and a little sweet. A nice heavy beer that has a near perfect finish with a hint of smooth alcohol. A beer that complements itself. This is a beer that will be on my list of regulars along side beers like DFH 90 minute IPA and Leinenkugels Big Eddy Russian Imperial Stout. A must try beer for all beer lovers.

Poured a large head with big white bubbles but didnt hold. Minimal carbonation and lacing. Color is a nice clear copper/amber. Has a sweet smell with hints of spices and fruit. Creamy and smooth but somewhat bland flavor compared to the aroma. The end has a very bitter finish. Pretty good beer but a little lacking in the flavor department I would drink it again but wouldnt seek it out.

Pours a small pure white head with very little lacing. Color is a nice clear light golden amber. Has a very pleasant citrus aroma. The taste is a little waxy and bitter, and the finish was a little overbearing. This beer is only ok and I may give it another shot but only if its on sale or given to me.
beer_name: Flying Dog Snake Dog IPA (2008 and later)

review_blob: Pours with a descent head and some lacing. It is kind of a hazy amber color, cloudy looking. There are faint hints of fruit, grass and hops but nothing really stands out. Pretty smooth up front and finishes kind of bitter with a bite of alcohol. Taste flavors of fruit, sweetness, hops, a little piney and some alcohol. I think this beer is an ok beer I would drink it again. At $6 a six pack its a good deal.

Nice clear amber/caramel color. Pours with a nice strong holding head and nice lacing. Slightly sweet smelling with hoppy, floral, fruity and citrus notes present. The flavor is much like the aroma but also offers hints of caramel and spice. Very smooth up front with a little bite of bitterness on the back ending with a very nice crisp and clean finish. This is a must try for all beer lovers and at $2.50 a bottle its a great deal.
